// ```

// ---

// **Key design decisions:**

// **`QuestionOption` as a separate table** instead of `String[]` — lets you attach `isCorrect`, `orderIndex`, and even an `imageUrl` per option cleanly. Your old schema stored options as `String[]` and `correctAnswer` as `String` which breaks for `MULTIPLE_SELECT`.

// **`StudentExamAnswer` has both `selectedOptionId` and `textAnswer`** — one will always be null depending on question type. This handles MCQ and text answers in one table cleanly.

// **Auto-grading flow:**
// ```
// MCQ / TRUE_FALSE    → compare selectedOptionId with isCorrect → auto marksAwarded
// SHORT_ANSWER / ESSAY → teacher manually sets marksAwarded + feedback
// MULTIPLE_SELECT     → compare selected options vs all isCorrect options → auto